result.name: Sushi Masa

reviews.text: Very good place. Great value set lunch. I just felt like I was back in Japan!

Just average, not impressive :( was expecting a little more in the freshness of fish, service and overall food quality. All staff doesn't smile and put down the tray really hard like they're very angry oops Sushi tasted quite warm which is weird to me, maybe the rice was too warm so it warmed up the fishes on top??!! Anyway they dont taste like wow, just slightly better than average... Maybe in comparison to 海睿 in Tung Chung, for the same price range for lunch sets, this resto's food quality is much lower. Eel rice was grilled quite well, the sauce was handles nicely too but there were a few bones which scare me a lot, so I probably won't visit again, not to mention their dinner is much more pricey. Interestingly they have omakase for lunch menu too.
Best value for money for fresh sushi
Authentic. Reasonably priced.
Horrible service. They didn't serve a dish and the waiter continued to argue they did. Didn't have a good experience here. Never came again.
